    "summary": "Thomas Widdershoven (Maastricht 1960) studied philosophy (MA), fine art and graphic design (BA). He is former creative director and chairman of the board of Design Academy Eindhoven. In 1993 he founded Thonik together with Nikki Gonnissen. Thonik collaborates with clients and creatives in design, e-culture, architecture, art, film and advertising. Thonik couples a strategic approach to an adventurous exploration of media. Clients include Hyundai Department Stores, Seoul, Museum Boijmans van Beuningen, the City of Nanjing, China, the City of Amsterdam, the Dutch Socialist Party (SP) and the Dutch TV network VPRO. Thonik has had solo exhibitions at the Shanghai Art Museum, The Venice Architecture Biennial, Spiral Art Center Tokyo, Moti Breda, Galerie Anatome and Institut N\u00e9erlandais Paris. Thonik's work is part of the permanent collection of the Centre Pompidou, Paris.  \n\nAs creative director of the Design Academy Eindhoven, he initiated four exhibitions at the Van Abbemuseum Eindhoven about the newest generation designers. These exhibitions travelled to New York, Suzhou, Shenzhen and Macau. He curated four graduationshows at the academy and four presentations in Milan. Since 2016 he is a guest professor at the Nanjing University, China. ",
